 interpolated directly into shell output that is `eval`'d on every prompt\n\nThe `handle` method captures `cwd` and inlines it unescaped into shell strings:\n\n```rust\nlet cwd = std::env::current_dir()?.to_string_lossy().to_string();\nmatch self.shell {\n    Shell::Bash | Shell::Zsh => println!(r#\"export _FLOX_HOOK_FIRED=\"{cwd}\";\"#),\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThis output is then `eval`'d by the bash/zsh hook:\n\n```bash\n_flox_vars=\"$(\"{flox_bin}\" hook-env --shell bash)\";\neval \"$_flox_vars\";\n```\n\nA directory named e.g. `/tmp/foo\";malicious_cmd;echo \"` would cause `eval` to execute `malicious_cmd`. The `cwd` needs to be shell-escaped (e.g. via `shlex`-style quoting) before interpolation, or the variable value should be set via a mechanism that doesn't require embedding the raw string into eval'd code (e.g. pass it as a base64-encoded export, or use `printf '%q'` style quoting on the shell side).\n\nhttps://github.com/flox/flox/blob/5c9e666ec74463a95a203dc13c3481319f95a5a3/cli/flox/src/commands/hook_env.rs#L21-L27\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)\n\n<sub>- If this code review was useful, please react with 👍. Otherwise, react with 👎.</sub>","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/flox/flox/issues/comments/4445480797/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":{"id":1236702,"client_id":"Iv23liqTIFEtdIu6Vn1r","slug":"claude","node_id":"A_kwHOBIuudM4AEt7e","owner":{"login":"anthropics","id":76263028,"node_id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjc2MjYzMDI4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/76263028?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/anthropics","html_url":"https://github.com/anthropics","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/anthropics/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/anthropics/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/anthropic